  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4591",
  "title": "Conflict between filters and pagination",
  "body": "Hello I'm trying to implement a search filtered by date that works with pagination and it's impossible to make them work together. Note: I am using instantSearch router to save queries in URL and trigger them onLoad.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// 1. Pagination is working (using refine(n) in a custom pagination widget) but date filters are not set yet\r\nhelper.search();\r\n\r\n// 2. Filters are working but pagination is not working (no Call made to Algolia when using pagination)\r\nhelper.setQueryParameter('filters', 'date_timestamp:1538352000 TO 1540944000')\r\n  .search();\r\n\r\n\r\n/* The next solutions to make date filters + pagination are not working */\r\n\r\n// Same result as 2.\r\nhelper.setQueryParameter('filters', 'date_timestamp:1538352000 TO 1540944000')\r\n  .setPage(helper.state.page)\r\n  .search();\r\n\r\n// Same result as 1.\r\nhelper.search(helper.state.query, {\r\n  page: helper.state.page,\r\n  filters: 'date_timestamp:1538352000 TO 1540944000',\r\n})\r\n\r\n// Seems to be working but 'helper.state.page' is not incremented when calling refine(n) in my custom widget\r\nhelper.setQueryParameter(\"filters\", filters)\r\n  .setQueryParameter(\"page\", helper.state.page)\r\n  .search()\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow am I supposed to make filtering and pagination work in the same search ?\r\nI am using **algoliasearch@4.8.0**.",
